    "strategy_description": "Heme (protoheme/heme B) production in S. cerevisiae using the entirely native heme biosynthesis pathway (KEGG module M00868). All 8 enzymatic steps (HEM1-HEM4, HEM12-HEM15) are present in iMM904. Strategy: (1) KO COX10/YPL172C to block protoheme degradation via heme O synthase; (2) Overexpress HEM1/YDR232W (rate-limiting ALA synthase, min flux 0.5); (3) Overexpress HEM12/YDR047W (uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase, min flux 0.5); (4) Overexpress HEM13/YDR044W (coproporphyrinogen oxidase, min flux 0.5). Added transport (PHEMEtm) and exchange (EX_pheme_c) reactions. Theoretical max 0.5502, optimized 0.5452 at 10% biomass (6% improvement over baseline 0.5141). Aerobic conditions required. Iron supplementation recommended."
